UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1943
1 three hundred fifty dollars ($350) nor more than five hundred dollars ($500)
2 and shall be imprisoned in the county jail for not less than seven (7) days nor
3 more than six (6) months and, in addition to fine and imprisonment, may be
4 sentenced to community labor for not less than ten (10) days nor more than
5 six (6) months. If any of the aggravating circumstances listed in subsection
6 (11) of this section are present, the mandatory minimum term of
7 imprisonment shall be fourteen (14) days, which term shall not be suspended,
8 probated, conditionally discharged, or subject to any other form of early
9 release;
10 (c) For a third offense within a ten (10) year period, be fined not less than five
11 hundred dollars ($500) nor more than one thousand dollars ($1,000) and shall
12 be imprisoned in the county jail for not less than thirty (30) days nor more
13 than twelve (12) months and may, in addition to fine and imprisonment, be
14 sentenced to community labor for not less than thirty (30) days nor more than
15 twelve (12) months. If any of the aggravating circumstances listed in
16 subsection (11) of this section are present, the mandatory minimum term of
17 imprisonment shall be sixty (60) days, which term shall not be suspended,
18 probated, conditionally discharged, or subject to any other form of early
19 release;
20 (d) 1. For a fourth or subsequent offense within a ten (10) year period, be:
21 a. Guilty of a Class D felony; and
22 b. Prohibited from purchasing alcohol during the period of license
23 suspension under KRS 189A.070 and for two (2) years following
24 the period of license suspension.
25 2. If any of the aggravating circumstances listed in subsection (11) of this
26 section are present, the mandatory minimum term of imprisonment shall
27 be two hundred forty (240) days, which term shall not be suspended,
Page 4 of 9
XXXX 2/4/2026 10:43 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1943
1 probated, conditionally discharged, or subject to any other form of
2 release; and
3 (e) For purposes of this subsection, prior offenses shall include all convictions in
4 this state, and any other state or jurisdiction, for operating or being in control
5 of a motor vehicle while under the influence of alcohol or other substances
6 that impair one's driving ability, or any combination of alcohol and such
7 substances, or while having an unlawful alcohol concentration, or driving
8 while intoxicated, but shall not include convictions for violating subsection
9 (1)(f) of this section. A court shall receive as proof of a prior conviction a
10 copy of that conviction, certified by the court ordering the conviction.
11 (6) Any person who violates the provisions of subsection (1)(f) of this section shall be
12 fined no less than one hundred dollars ($100) and no more than five hundred dollars
13 ($500), or sentenced to twenty (20) hours of community service in lieu of a fine. A
14 person subject to the penalties of this subsection shall not be subject to the penalties
15 established in subsection (5) of this section or any other penalty established
16 pursuant to KRS Chapter 189A, except those established in KRS 189A.040(1) and
17 KRS 189A.070.
18 (7) If the person is under the age of twenty-one (21) and there was an alcohol
19 concentration of 0.08 or greater[ based on the definition of alcohol concentration in
20 KRS 189A.005], the person shall be subject to the penalties established pursuant to
21 subsection (5) of this section.
22 (8) (a) For a second or third offense within a ten (10) year period, the minimum
23 sentence of imprisonment or community labor shall not be suspended,
24 probated, or subject to conditional discharge or other form of early release.
25 (b) For a fourth or subsequent offense under this section, the minimum term of
26 imprisonment shall be one hundred twenty (120) days, and this term shall not
27 be suspended, probated, or subject to conditional discharge or other form of
Page 5 of 9
