UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1943
1 early release.
2 (c) For a second or subsequent offense, at least forty-eight (48) hours of the
3 mandatory sentence shall be served consecutively.
4 (9) When sentencing persons under subsection (5)(a) of this section, at least one (1) of
5 the penalties shall be assessed and that penalty shall not be suspended, probated, or
6 subject to conditional discharge or other form of early release.
7 (10) In determining the ten (10) year period under this section, the period shall be
8 measured from the dates on which the offenses occurred for which the judgments of
9 conviction were entered.
10 (11) For purposes of this section, aggravating circumstances are any one (1) or more of
11 the following:
12 (a) Operating a motor vehicle in excess of thirty (30) miles per hour above the
13 speed limit;
14 (b) Operating a motor vehicle in the wrong direction on a limited access highway;
15 (c) Operating a motor vehicle that causes an accident resulting in death or serious
16 physical injury as defined in KRS 500.080;
17 (d) Operating a motor vehicle while the alcohol concentration in the operator's
18 blood or breath is 0.15 or more as measured by a test or tests of a sample of
19 the operator's blood or breath taken within two (2) hours of cessation of
20 operation of the motor vehicle;
21 (e) Refusing to submit to any test or tests of one's blood, breath, or urine
22 requested by an officer having reasonable grounds to believe the person was
23 operating or in physical control of a motor vehicle in violation of subsection
24 (1) of this section, except it shall not be considered an aggravating
25 circumstance for a first offense under subsection (5)(a) of this section; and
26 (f) Operating a motor vehicle that is transporting a passenger under the age of
27 twelve (12) years old.
