1 (12) The substances applicable to a prosecution under subsection (1)(d) of this section
2 are:
3 (a) Any Schedule I controlled substance except marijuana;
4 (b) Alprazolam;
5 (c) Amphetamine;
6 (d) Buprenorphine;
7 (e) Butalbital;
8 (f) Carisoprodol;
9 (g) Cocaine;
10 (h) Diazepam;
11 (i) Hydrocodone;
12 (j) Meprobamate;
13 (k) Methadone;
14 (l) Methamphetamine;
15 (m) Oxycodone;
16 (n) Promethazine;
17 (o) Propoxyphene; and
18 (p) Zolpidem.
19 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 189A IS CREATED TO
20 READ AS FOLLOWS:
21 Any ignition interlock license issued under KRS 189A.340 or hardship license issued
22 under KRS 189A.410 for any person who is prohibited from purchasing alcohol after a
23 fourth or subsequent conviction of Section 1 of this Act shall contain:
24 (a) A prominent display of the language "No Alcohol Sale"; and
25 (b) Other security features identifying the person as being prohibited from
26 purchasing alcohol, including a prominent red stripe on the front of the license.
27 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 507 IS CREATED TO
Page 7 of 9
XXXX 2/4/2026 10:43 AM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1943
1 READ AS FOLLOWS:
2 (1) In addition to any other penalty provided by law, any person convicted of an
3 offense under this chapter in which the victim's death results from the
4 defendant's operation of a motor vehicle under the influence of alcohol, a
5 controlled substance, or other substance as described in Section 1 of this Act
6 shall be prohibited from purchasing alcohol:
7 (a) During any period of probation, shock probation, parole, conditional
8 discharge, or any other form of early release; and
9 (b) For two (2) years following any period of supervision described under
10 paragraph (a) of this subsection.
11 (2) The court shall:
12 (a) Designate in its judgment if the victim's death resulted from the defendant's
13 operation of a motor vehicle under the influence of alcohol, a controlled
14 substance, or other substance as described in Section 1 of this Act;
15 (b) Order the defendant to surrender his or her license to operate a motor
16 vehicle to the court. Should the defendant fail to surrender his or her
17 license to the court, the court shall issue an order directing the sheriff or
18 any other peace officer to seize the license immediately and deliver it to the
19 court. The court shall then forward the license to the Transportation
20 Cabinet; and
21 (c) Transmit the conviction records and other appropriate information to the
22 Transportation Cabinet.
23 SECTION 4. A NEW SECTION OF KRS 186.400 TO 186.640 IS CREATED
24 TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
25 Any person prohibited from purchasing alcohol upon a fourth or subsequent
26 conviction under Section 1 of this Act, or a conviction of an offense under Section 3 of
27 this Act in which the death results from the defendant's operation of a motor vehicle
Page 8 of 9
