UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1943
1 under the influence of alcohol, a controlled substance, or other substance as described
2 in Section 1 of this Act, shall only be eligible for issuance of an operator's license that
3 contains:
4 (1) A prominent display of the language "No Alcohol Sale"; and
5 (2) Other security features identifying the person as being prohibited from
6 purchasing alcohol, including a prominent red stripe on the front of the license.
7 SECTION 5. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 244 IS CREATED TO
8 READ AS FOLLOWS:
9 A retail licensee, or the licensee's agent, servant, or employee shall not knowingly sell,
10 give away, or deliver any alcoholic beverage, or knowingly procure or permit any
11 alcoholic beverage to be sold, given away, possessed by, or delivered to a person who is
12 prohibited from purchasing alcohol upon:
13 (1) A fourth or subsequent conviction under Section 1 of this Act; or
14 (2) A conviction of an offense under Section 3 of this Act in which the victim's death
15 results from the defendant's operation of a motor vehicle under the influence of
16 alcohol, a controlled substance, or other substance as described in Section 1 of
17 this Act.
